      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i keep getting a 500 error on the /api/v1/checkout/process endpoint whenever a user has multiple items in their cart with different discount codes applied. here are the logs from the last few occurrences:\n\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] ERROR: Unexpected null pointer in DiscountService.calculateTotal()\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] STACKTRACE: com.ecommerce.service.DiscountService.applyPromotions(DiscountService.java:142)\n[2023-10-27 14:25:12] ERROR: Atomic operation failed: Database transaction timed out during lock acquisition\n[2023-10-27 14:25:12] STACKTRACE: com.ecommerce.db.TransactionManager.commit(TransactionManager.java:89)\n\nseems like it might be a race condition or something with the logic handling the stack of applied promos, but i cant tell for sure. what's causing this?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
